content:
mikoraiden writes...
@gordongekko what firms have you heard from? Also, do you mind sharing your stats if you're comfortable :)
Interviews with KWM, HSF and Corrs. Have been rejected by White & Case, and ghosted by Clifford Chance (presume rejected). Go8, >75 WAM, T6 Para – don't want to give much more detail to avoid dox – sorry.

@whirlingthepool
Thanks!
Yeah – so it's the legal stream but the role is in policy so you can do your PLT too

@Icetea123
Thank you thank you. Yeah actually realised I got it yesterday, just was in my spam inbox lol
Did anyone get the CU interviewer who is in a completely different practice group they expressed their interest in?

@Jelly 55
Really appreciate your encouragement and advice! Yeah I really wished it could be the partner from my interested area but I guess the HR person is there as well.
Do we all have the P&D Manager or that is also random? I can't imagine she sits on 60+ interviews...

@goldenm2020
I haven’t received anything additional from Clayton either but my interview was also this week yesterday actually!
And yeah mine went for 30 minutes and they didn’t ask about practice areas I was interested in but I did get asked what type of client work I would like to do like working with individual or companies if that means anything.

@shepherdfan
Just to clarify, you mean the coffee catch up is for the grad role??? Or simply because they think someone would receive multiple offers and the partner is trying to really sell the firm to the applicant?
Honestly I am too confused already with this process.

@auzlawz
Do you mind to share which area your interview partner is in?
It is def positive they are introducing you to the associate within the practice area, however I personally think Clutz is really keen on candidates to retain their offers. Must had few rejections from the clerks last year.

@watermelon123 I found this on the Melbourne Thread, I'm not sure how up-to-date it is, but it was really helpful in answering questions on offers and included stuff on preferences. I would recommend anyone who wants to know more about what happens on offer day to check it out. It really helped me.
https://drive.google.com/fil e/d/1k5A_MKUTXbUroljaf0_9WAjzV-6MG-Xc/view?usp=sharing
Also good luck everyone for tomorrow wishing you all the best outcomes (including myself ahh!!).

@ravencraw
Congrats on Minters!!
At least you have one firm, no need to feel stressed

@Icetea123
You are smashing it damn.
That many firms damn.

@auzlawz
Also I thought CU already send out rejections?
Maybe your partner is busy? But also at the same time an offer email should come through by now

@auzlawz @bingl3
Thanks ahhahah just want to be as helpful as I could
This process is hard and heartbreaking enough, glad I could bring some positive energy :)

Thank you @Goldenm2020!
@Tryingtolaw I've got 4 years non-law work experience, then 2 years working as a law clerk, low GPA, volunteering in pro bono since first year and societies, lots of legal competitions as well.
@lawclerk-2024 I got an offer for paralegal as well at another firm

@Jelly55 @auzlawz
So sorry to hear you guys got rejected by Clutz, unsure what really happened. Now I think the meeting after the interview could be a second vibe check really, I saw someone at Melb thread also talking about this.
Luckily both of you have other things to do so all the best!

@auzlawz that’s great news mid tier is just as good as top tier firms  i genuinely hope everything goes well and you enjoy it.
At least the anticipation and wait is finally over. Of course it would have been nice to get a taste of working at CU but guess wasn’t meant to be this time of round but yes like you said it was great to get even a glimpse and at least opportunity to try.
All the best to you as well!

Lawclerk7292 writes...
@auslaw003 they asked when they called to reject me. In the interview it was a bit odd, they wrote down the other firms I was interviewing at and then the reasons why I said Hall & Wilcox was better, it gave me weird vibes.
Okay, that is extremely weird. I thought I'd heard good things about their culture, but based on that experience, I'd honestly be glad not to have to work there.

Icetea123 writes...
@auslaw003 they did the same when I rejected their offer, and also asked who else I was interviewing with + reasons H&W is better during the interview. I definitely found it odd.
Yeah honestly, I don't get why they would ask that during the interview at all, it's so weird. It's also not exactly a great question either. In my opinion, it's pretty hard to separate a lot of the firms apart from their overall bands (top tier, mid tier etc. but even that is somewhat subjective). I would've just said I would find any firm who actually gave me an offer to be the best one :D

lahaine writes...
@Clerkshippy Did you end up getting a grad role? Or are you applying again?
fortunate to have received a graduate spot at a TT firm – dm me if you have any specific questions about the process (-:

lingolover writes...
@lawyeroneday haha no, just assuming the worst
Ah, ok. Back to assuming the worst for me too then, lol.

@Kapool
FWIW I have an 80s WAM (Go8) and was rejected by Allens. I’m all for the process being as holistic and meritocratic as possible, but we’re talking about the top-of-top tiers here. Firms like Allens have the pulling power to choose from a range of 76+WAM-social-butterfly-unicorns who tick every box that Allens want ticked.
This process is demoralising enough and coming into it with any sense of entitlement or expectations about what individual firms owe you is only going to make life miserable.

hydr8 writes...
hello! does anyone have any experience with melb OPP  assessment centre and share what its like? thank you in advance.
@hydr8 Someone at my uni (non-G8) did it last Thursday: they said there were three groups of seven people each — they worked on two criminal law problems as a group.

@Matchachaw
Yes, I received it on Monday and my interview is scheduled Thursday next week. I believe it is the last day for the interview?
I would strongly suggest you email HR asap....

@hopeforanoffer
From my understanding it is more of a vibe check. Like ur confidence level, how well you explained your behaviour questions examples etc.
I am unsure what is ur WAM like, if there are particular concerns like failed corp law, during the interview the partner will generally ask.

also forgot
@orca99 nothing from TG or PM
@butterworths nothing from H&W
lander & rogers +1 psych
